    Iterable<TypeDefinition>, AnnotatedCodeElement, ByteCodeElement, DeclaredByType, ModifierReviewable, NamedElement, NamedElement.WithRuntimeName, TypeDefinition, TypeDescription, TypeVariableSource
    Enclosing class:
    TypeDescription.ForLoadedType

    public static class TypeDescription.ForLoadedType.WithEagerProperties
extends TypeDescription.ForLoadedType
    A type description of a loaded type that resolves any field, constructor or method property eagerly, i.e. calls all of Class.getDeclaredFields(), Class.getDeclaredMethods(), Class.getDeclaredConstructors() and Class.getDeclaredClasses(). This might trigger a NoClassDefFoundError if any such element refers to an type that is not available to this class loader.

        public FieldList<FieldDescription.InDefinedShape> getDeclaredFields()
        Description copied from interface: TypeDefinition
        Returns the fields that this type declares. A super type is only defined for non-generic types (TypeDefinition.Sort.NON_GENERIC), parameterized types (TypeDefinition.Sort.PARAMETERIZED) or generic array types (TypeDefinition.Sort.GENERIC_ARRAY) types. Generic array types never define fields and the returned list is always empty for such types.
